{"chunk_id": "github_pr_1237_comment_2010722811", "source_type": "reviews", "pairs": [{"instruction": "I'm implementing an `AliasTable` in my code, and I noticed that it's receiving pointers but not freeing them. This could lead to memory leaks. How should I handle this?", "response": "You need to ensure proper resource management by either manually cleaning up the pointers in the deinit function or transferring ownership of the pointers to the `AliasTable`. This will prevent memory leaks and ensure that all resources are properly freed when they're no longer needed."}], "user_id": "Nick"}
