{"chunk_id": "github_pr_1141_comment_1976745202", "source_type": "reviews", "pairs": [{"instruction": "I'm working on a multi-user environment where multiple users can use worldedit commands. I noticed that the current implementation stores worldedit positions in the command file, which could lead to one user's position being overwritten by another. How can I modify this to ensure each user has their own set of positions without interference?", "response": "You should store these positions within the user struct using `source.pos1` and `source.pos2`. This approach ensures that each user has their own separate set of positions, preventing any interference between users. Additionally, consider thread safety to handle concurrent access if multiple users are editing simultaneously."}], "user_id": "Nick"}
