{"chunk_id": "github_pr_2824_comment_3183957328", "source_type": "reviews", "pairs": [{"instruction": "I added a static buffer of size 20 for nodes directly into the per-entity component struct. However, I'm concerned about memory waste and potential arbitrary limits on node count. How should I handle this?", "response": "Avoid adding fixed-size buffers like [20]main.entityModel.EntityModel.Node directly to the component struct. This approach imposes an arbitrary limit on node count and wastes memory for entities with fewer nodes. Instead, consider storing node references in a separate, dynamically sized collection such as a linked list or arena-allocated array outside the component struct. This ensures O(1) growth without fixed upper bounds and decouples component layout from implementation details."}], "user_id": "Nick"}
