{"chunk_id": "github_pr_2604_comment_2862646546", "source_type": "reviews", "pairs": [{"instruction": "Can you review this approach: The original code calls parsePosition three times, once per axis, passing the player's position component as an offset. This duplicated parsing logic and made it harder to ensure consistent handling of missing arguments or malformed input across axes.", "response": "This approach can be improved by calling parseCoordinates once with the remaining split iterator, allowing it to fill all three coordinates atomically. This change centralizes coordinate parsing, reduces code size, and ensures that any validation or error handling performed in parseCoordinates applies uniformly to all axes. It aligns with the architectural pattern used elsewhere where a single parser is reused rather than multiple thin wrappers."}], "user_id": "Nick"}
