{"chunk_id": "github_pr_1478_comment_2133640661", "source_type": "reviews", "pairs": [{"instruction": "I'm trying to update the inventory system to support separate crafting stations, but I'm unsure how to handle storing tool types without relying on specific implementation details. The current code directly stores `toolTypes.items[currentToolType]` in the inventory struct field `.workbench`, which seems fragile.", "response": "To maintain type safety and prepare for future architectural changes like separate crafting stations, you should store only an index into the global tool list instead of directly storing the item. Change `.workbench` to hold `{.index = @intCast(currentToolType)}`. Additionally, update the label update from accessing `.id` directly on the item to calling a method `id()`. This approach eliminates reliance on concrete layout details and ensures that your code can handle different station arrays without breaking."}], "user_id": "Nick"}
