{"chunk_id": "github_pr_1530_comment_2159975183", "source_type": "reviews", "pairs": [{"instruction": "I'm working on the SbbGen module and encountered an issue where the server crashes when the 'structure' parameter is missing or the referenced building block can't be found. How should I handle this?", "response": "Replace the `unreachable` calls with explicit error messages logged via `main.utils.panicWithMessage`. This will preserve runtime safety while still failing fast on truly invalid data, aligning with the project's policy of explicit failure over silent crashes."}], "user_id": "Nick"}
