{"chunk_id": "github_pr_809_comment_1871612337", "source_type": "reviews", "pairs": [{"instruction": "Can you review this approach: The code uses openWindow to handle both creating new windows and reopening existing ones, which leads to issues like memory leaks because onClose is never called before onOpenFn.", "response": "This approach violates the single responsibility principle by mixing window creation with lifecycle management. It results in memory leaks as resources from previous notifications are not properly freed. To address this, introduce a new reopenWindow function that first calls onClose on the existing instance (if any), then proceeds with allocation and onOpenFn. This separation ensures that openWindow only creates fresh windows, while reopenWindow handles transitions safely, preserving modularity and preventing resource leaks."}], "user_id": "Nick"}
